         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To Jupiter Optimus Maximus Dolichenus, for the safety and victory of our lords the three Augusti and <note>erased name</note> and the 
               return of the emperors to their own city. Titus Flavius <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>arinus, legionary centurion, willingly paid his vow. 
               b. Dedicated on the 11th of April.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
          <!--   <p>a.4: Geta has the title Augustus in Tripolitanian inscriptions as early as 201, see <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0913">913</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0914">914</ref>, 
               <ref type="inscription" n="IRT0915">915</ref></p>
            <p>a.6: line 5 and 6, deliberately erased, contained perhaps the name of <foreign xml:lang="la">C. Fulvius Plautianus</foreign>, or that of the dedicator's legion, possibly 
               <foreign xml:lang="la">III Augusta</foreign>, disbanded in 238, or <foreign xml:lang="la">III Gallica</foreign>, disbanded under Elagabalus.
               Detachments of <foreign xml:lang="la">III Gallica</foreign> served in Africa in the time of Septimius Severus.</p>
            <p>b) line 1. 11th April, the birthday of Septimius Severus.</p> -->
